Remo Stars are looking to sign Doma United striker Charles Chubuike ahead of the second half of the season. Head coach of the Ikenne club, Daniel Ogunmodede, disclosed exclusively to DAILY POST that Chubike’s upfront attribute will be a plus to his team. He, however, stressed that other options are being considered alongside promoting players from the team’s academy. “We are looking at the possibility of signing Doma United striker Charles Chubike ahead of the second half of the season,” begins Ogunmodede. “His physiques and movement upfront can be of help to our team. “We are looking at other options in attack and we are also looking at the possibility of bringing players in from our academy. Remo Stars FC is currently occupying the fifth position in the Nigeria Premier League Group A standings.